The evidence with the title 'How long will the U.S. oil reserves last? | HowStuffWorks ' says In june 2011, president Obama announced that 30 million barrels would be released from the Strategic Oil Reserves , leaving about 697 million barrels in the reserve .  ... For all the discussion surrounding this decision , the oil released amounted to only about two - thirds of average daily 87 - million -barrelglobalconsumption.
